{
  "text": "A linear map satisfying the above identity is called a Jordan derivation. In [CITATION_1] it is proved that any Jordan derivation on a semi-prime algebra is a derivation. Since every von Neumann algebra M is semi-prime (i.e. aMa = {0} implies that a = {0}), in order to prove that a 2-local derivation \u25b3 : M \u2192 M is a derivation it is sufficient to show that the map \u25b3 : M \u2192 M is additive.",
